Civil Society, grassroots organisations and community- based groups across Yoruba territories are working to set up a committee that will mediate and reconcile the warring Asiwaju Bola Ahmed Tinubu, All Progressive Congress (APC) National Leader and Ogbeni Rauf Aregbesola, Minister for Interior. The group under the aegis of the League of South West Civil Society and Community Based Organisations while addressing newsmen in Lagos, Taiwo Adeleye, the Convener said the group will brief the people on the outcome of the people driven peace initiative. “We have called this important meeting for many good reasons. 2022 IWD: NGO To Gift 100 Traders, Street Sweepers Food Items 2023: Hope Alive As Gov Emmanuel Reviews Ongoing Projects In… We are all conscious of the history of politics in the South West for time immemorial. “In the South West, post-colonial history teaches us that the region had its dose of intra-party wrangling with far-reaching consequences on Yoruba people and their ancestral territories. The Western regional crisis which dovetailed into the 1964 general elections could have been avoided. It started as an ideological difference between the then Premier of Western Region, Chief Obafemi Awolowo and his deputy, Chief Ladoke Akintola. Eventually, this crisis snowballed into a major conflict within the Action Group (AG) leading to the emergence of a faction of Chief Akintola presented as an alternative political front that clashed with the established dominion of the Action Group.